<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-11-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-11-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram per cable.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward to Mr. Johnson. </persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-11-26"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 26, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Let San Juan rest. Claims convention unless amended is useless. Wait for
                            dispatches Friday or Saturday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Reverdy Johnson,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c.:</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>